SCENE 7 — THE FAINT WRONGNESS (approach; transition out)
=====================================================================
The dragons are gone — banked away, dwindling, the sky empty again. Relief. And then, as the road
finally bends toward the mountain's foot, the first hairline crack in the world.

READ ALOUD: "The two shadows shrink into the east and are gone, and the breath you didn't know
you were holding goes out of all of you at once. The road drops toward a valley, and at the
bottom of it, small and grey against the immensity of the mountain behind it, sits Ivarstead. You
are nearly there. And it's nothing, really — you'd miss it if you weren't raw from a day of being
hunted — but as the cart rolls down the last mile, you each catch it, once: a footprint in the
mud of the road that appears a heartbeat BEFORE Bjorn's boot comes down to make it. A word
someone said, echoing back off the rocks a moment too late, in their own voice. Small. Barely
there. The faintest edge of something the closer you get, the worse it will be.
   The mountain waits. And the time on it is already beginning to come loose."

